How to Use

1. Enable the Extension

Click the extension icon in your browser toolbar. Ensure “Enable Clips UI” is checked.

2. Open a YouTube Video

Go to a YouTube video. A 'CLIPS' button will appear in the bottom-right corner, click it to open the clip sidebar.

3. Create a Clip

Play the video to your  start point, Click 'Start', Play to the end point, Click 'End'.

Your clip will be saved to the history & copied to your clipboard automatically.

4. Manage Clips
Click a clip to copy its link again. Double-click a clip to rename it. Click ❌ to delete a clip.

5. Export Clips

Export (basic): Copies all clip URLs

Export + Labels: Includes labels or video titles

Independent Export (recommended): Copies clips in this format:

Label | v=VIDEO_ID&start=START&end=END

This format is compatible with the clip player website

6. Use the Clip Player

Open your clip player using the popup button

Paste your exported clips into the input box

Click 'Input Clips'

Click 'Start' 

Clips are stored locally in your browser
No data is sent externally
Works best with standard YouTube video pages
